verses.roman:
saṅkṣepe kahiluṅ ei jhālira vicāra
'rāghavera jhāli' bali' vikhyāti yāhāra

synonyms: saṅkṣepe—in brief; kahiluṅ—l have spoken; ei jhālira—of these bags; vicāra—the description; rāghavera jhāli—the bags of Rāghava; bali'-as; vikhyāti—the fame; yāhāra—of which.
translation: Thus I have briefly described the bags that have become famous as rāghavera jhāli.
